{
  "texts": [
    "Cold nuclear matter effectsCold nuclear matter effects generally refer to all modifications present in pA collisions, when there is a nuclear target, but not in pp collisions.",
    "These effects are referred to as being \"cold\" in the sense that it is assumed that no quarkgluon plasma is created.",
    "Note that this assumption may be challenged in high-multiplicity pp and pA collisions.",
    "These effects are also presented in AA collisions when quark-gluon plasma is also created.",
    "The nuclear modifications of the parton distributions (nPDF effects) are typically included by a parameterization such as the EPPS16 [138] parameterization."
  ]
}